Chet, allow me to push the button of hopes springs eternal. I think the gang at POV will keep this site rolling. and interactive.  With the media attention beginning, (I have not seen Hollis the Reporter/Gannett News Service)'s article about this, but he did talk to alot of us, and they service 120 so so papers so....Out there in the real world must be some corporate type's who are also viet nam vets, or what ever, needing write off's.  I remain opptimistic. Why not? It is easier to bo opptimistic then pessimestic.  and less depressing.<br><br>
Friendly advice, I don't think you have lost the fire, you have too much depth for that.  Perhaps just time to re adjust the wick is all.<br><br>
I also think of the Sundays of May as tough, what with Mothers day (11th), Armed Forces day (17th) and the two Memorial days (26th the holiday and 30th, the real day), and<br>
I think all of these are real sneaky, real emotional, I mean we have Mothers and Soldiers back to back, talk about heart strings.  <br><br>
What would happen if we ever had a &quot;protestors&quot; holiday?. Would Jane Fonda sing the National anthem as a gesture of healing?  A softball game between SDS and Young Americans for Freedom? A 10K jungle run?  Oh, the mind is overwhelmed with the potential (for mayhem?) or merriment.  Let it flow Chet, you still have too much to contribute.  Hey, I won't even bill you for this one.<br><br>
